Date: 7/10/1933
Source: Press, The
Author:
Vol / Page: 15
Edition:
Quote: <i>Crutch.</i> (1) to cut away the wool round a sheep's tail and hind legs so that he will not foul himself. (2) When sheep are dipped they are shoved under with a thing like an inverted <i>crutch.</i> This is called <i>crutching.</i> (3) The implement used for (2). (C.)
Notes: (Acland Gloss.)

