Date: 0/0/1955
Source: Wool Away!
Author: BOWEN
Vol / Page: 53
Edition:
Quote: I am of the opinion that crutching can be overdone, as well as underdone. No more wool should be taken off than is necessary to keep the sheep clean, and to allow the lamb to feed and find the teats easily, for heavy crutching can spoil the fleece when it comes to shearing time, causing a large quantity of half-wool pieces.
Notes:

